
## API

The API is split into 3 core modules:

* [entry]({{@root.baseUrl}}/{{#getModulePageName 'entry'}}{{/getModulePageName}}): methods relating to managers and their stats.
* [league]({{@root.baseUrl}}/{{#getModulePageName 'league'}}{{/getModulePageName}}): methods to lookup league details and entries.
* [fpl]({{@root.baseUrl}}/{{#getModulePageName 'fpl'}}{{/getModulePageName}}): methods relating to the FPL game in general.

## Exceptions

* All methods return promises and exceptions should be caught in a catch handler.
* Please refer to the [error codes]({{baseUrl}}/Error-Codes) page.

## TypeScript

* fpl-api-node is packaged with TypeScript definitions.

## Caching

* By default all http requests are cached by default for 30 minutes.
* Requests that will never change (such as finished gameweeks) will be cached forever.


## Available fpl endpoints

fpl-api-node is simply a wrapper extracting data from various endpoints.

For those wanting to access these directly the available endpoints are:

 * https://fantasy.premierleague.com/drf/bootstrap-static
 * https://fantasy.premierleague.com/drf/entry/${id}
 * https://fantasy.premierleague.com/drf/entry/${id}/history
 * https://fantasy.premierleague.com/drf/entry/${id}/event/{$event}/picks
 * https://fantasy.premierleague.com/drf/entry/${id}/transfers
 * https://fantasy.premierleague.com/drf/teams
 * https://fantasy.premierleague.com/drf/elements
 * https://fantasy.premierleague.com/drf/events
 * https://fantasy.premierleague.com/drf/game-settings
 * https://fantasy.premierleague.com/drf/event/${event}/live
 * https://fantasy.premierleague.com/drf/leagues-classic-standings/${id}
